The paper discusses the use of a conditional-GAN framework for image recovery, specifically for facial information recovery. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of a multi-component loss function, which involves regression loss, indicating the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI). The use of a GAN also falls under the machine learning sub-category (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of U-Net architecture, which is commonly used in image segmentation tasks (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions that the research is carried out as a part of a facial recognition software, indicating the use of multimedia techniques (cs.MM).
